name: the land
description: 'the hard surface of the earth, when compared to the area covered by sea'

name: the soil
description: 'the substance that plants naturally grow in'

name: the dust
description: 'dry powder consisting of extremely small bits of matter, found outside or inside buildings'

name: the mud
description: 'wet earth that has become soft and sticky'

name: the cliff or precipice
description: 'a high rock with a very steep side (often near the sea)'

name: the mainland
description: 'the main area of land that forms a country, as compared to islands near it'

name: the shore
description: 'the land along the edge of a large body of water, such as an ocean or a lake'

name: the ocean
description: 'any of the world's major bodies of salt water'; generally larger than 'sea'

name: the bay
description: 'an area of the sea that curves inwards towards the land'

name: the lagoon
description: 'a body of sea water partly or completely separated from the sea by sand, rock etc., generally smaller than a bay’

name: the reef
description: 'a line mass of sharp rocks, often made of coral, near the surface of the sea'

name: the cape
description: 'a large piece of land surrounded on three sides by the sea'

name: the tide
description: 'the regular rising and lowering of the level of the sea'

name: the whirlpool
description: 'a powerful current of water that spins around and can pull things down into it'

name: the bolt of lightning
description: 'a flash of lightning and a noise of thunder together, which hits something'

name: the fire
description: ‘a fire lit deliberately for heating or cooking’

name: the embers
description: 'pieces of wood or coal in a fire that are no longer burning but are still red and very hot'

name: to burn(2)
description: 'be on fire, be consumed by fire'

name: the match
description: 'a small wooden stick used to light a fire'

name: the baby
description: ‘very young human that cannot walk yet’

name: the family
description: ‘group of closely related relatives, consisting minimally of parents and children’

name: he/she/it
description: (third person singular pronoun, regardless of gender/sex)

name: the animal
description: 'living creature that can move (including or excluding humans)'

name: the livestock
description: 'domestic mammals kept for service or for useful products (cows, horses, donkeys, sheep, goats, pigs, reindeer, camels, etc.)'

name: the pasture
description: 'land or field that is covered with grass and is used for livestock to feed on'

name: the herdsman
description: 'a man who looks after a herd of animals'

name: the stable or stall
description: 'building where domestic animals (any kind, not just horses) are kept'

name: the ox
description: 'a castrated bull, often used for working on farms'

name: the mule
description: 'an animal that has a donkey and a horse as parents'

name: the fowl
description: 'a bird that is kept for its meat and eggs'

name: the chicken
description: (Fill in only if there is a general term for 'rooster or hen'.)

name: the fin
description: 'one of the thin body parts that a fish uses to swim'

name: the scale
description: 'one of the small flat pieces of skin that cover the bodies of fish'

name: the nit
description: 'an egg of a louse that is sometimes found in people's hair'

name: the sandfly or midge or gnat
the skin or hide
description: (skin: of a human; hide: of an animal)

name: the temples
description: ‘the two fairly flat areas on each side of people’s forehead’, or more generally ‘the two sides of people’s head’

name: the jaw
description: ‘the lower part of people’s face that moves when they eat’

name: to blink
description: ‘to shut and open one’s eyes quickly’

name: the claw
description: ‘the sharp curved nail on the toe of an animal or bird’

name: the thigh
description: ‘the top part of the leg, between the knee and the hip’

name: the udder
description: ‘the part of a cow/female goat/... that hangs down between its back legs and that produces milk’

name: the buttocks
description: ‘the fleshy part of one’s body that people sit on’

name: to dribble
description: ‘to let saliva flow out of one’s mouth onto one’s chin’

name: the goitre/goiter
description: ‘a disease of the thyroid gland that makes one’s neck very swollen’

name: the boil
description: ‘a painful infected swelling under someone’s skin’

name: to choke
description: 'prevent from breathing (not necessarily leading to death)’

name: the pot
description: 'a container used for cooking which is round, deep, and usually made of metal'

name: the kettle
description: 'a metal container with a lid, a handle, and a spout (= for pouring), used to boil water'

name: the pan
description: 'a round and relatively flat metal container used for cooking, with one long handle'

name: the dish
description: 'a relatively flat, round vessel from which food is served on the table'

name: the plate
description: 'a flat and usually round vessel that you eat from'

name: the bowl
description: ‘a concave container that is open at the top, usually used to hold food’

name: the jug/pitcher
description: 'a container for holding and pouring liquids with a handle and a spout'

name: the cup
description: ‘a drinking vessel not made of glass’

name: the saucer
description: 'a small dish for placing a cup'

name: the knife(1)
description: 'knife for eating' (as opposed to knife used for preparing food)

name: the fork
description: 'tool used for picking up and eating food, with a handle and three or four points'

name: the tongs
description: 'a tool that consists of two movable bars joined at one end, used to pick up an object'

name: the meal
description: 'an occasion when one eats food, for example breakfast or lunch'

name: the breakfast
description: 'the meal one has in the morning'

name: the lunch
description: 'a meal eaten in the middle of the day'

name: the dinner
description: 'the main meal of the day, eaten in the middle of the day or in the evening'

name: to peel
description: 'remove the skin from food or vegetables'

name: to sieve or to strain
description: 'separate solid things from a liquid by pouring the mixture through a sieve (= a container with very small holes in it)'

name: to scrape
description: 'remove something from a surface, using the edge of a knife, stick, etc.'

name: the bread
description: 'a common important food made from flour, water, and yeast'

name: the dough
description: 'a mixture of flour and water ready to be baked into bread, pastry etc.'

name: to knead
description: 'press a dough many times with one's hands'

name: to crush or to grind
description: 'press [grain] in order to break it into very small pieces or powder'

name: the mortar(1)
description: 'a hard bowl in which substances are crushed with a pestle'

name: the pestle
description: 'a short stick with a heavy round end, used for crushing things in a mortar'

name: the meat
description: 'the flesh of animals or birds eaten as food'

name: the vegetables
description: 'an edible plant grown in gardens that is not sweet'

name: the fruit
description: generic name for tree fruit covering apples, pears, mangos, oranges, etc.

name: the bunch
description: 'a group of flowers/fruit that are held together'

name: the oil
description: 'a smooth, thick liquid made from plants or animals, used especially in cooking'

name: the pepper
description: 'black pepper, a table seasoning produced from the berries of the plant Piper nigrum'

name: the yolk
description: 'the yellow part in the centre of an egg'

name: to spin
description: 'to draw out and twist fiber into thread'

name: the spindle
description: 'a stick used in spinning fiber into thread'

name: the awl
description: 'pointed tool for marking or piercing wood or leather'

name: the (woman's) dress
description: 'garment worn by women over the torso extending to the legs'

name: the plait/braid
description: ‘a length of hair that has been separated into three parts and then woven together’

name: the yard or court
description: ‘enclosed area atttached to a house, whether outside or an inner court’

name: the shelf
description: ‘a long flat narrow board fixed onto a wall or in a frame or cupboard, used for putting things on or stroing things on’

name: the trough
description: ‘a long narrow open container that holds water or food for animals’

name: the thatch
description: ‘natural roofing material such as straw, reeds, leaves, etc.’

name: the ridgepole
description: 'the highest horizontal beam in a roof'

name: the rafter
description: 'a horizontal beam that supports the roof'

name: the post or pole
description: = ‘a strong upright piece of wood, metal etc. that is fixed into the ground, especially to support something’

name: the mortar(2)
description: 'a mixture of lime, sand and water, used in building for joining bricks or stones together'

name: the adobe
description: ‘earth and straw that are made into bricks for building houses’

name: the ditch
description: ‘a long narrow hole cut into the ground at the side of a field, road etc., especially for water to flow through’

name: the spade
description: 'tool with handle and blade used for digging in the ground'

name: the shovel
description: 'tool with handle and scoop for lifting and throwing material such as soil'

name: the hoe
description: 'tool with handle and blade with two or more prongs used for weeding, raking, etc.'

name: the cassava/manioc
description: (the tuber, rather than its plant or products)

name: the fish poison
description: (in Amazonia, a kind of root is apparently used as fish poison)

name: to strike or hit or beat
the adze
description: 'a sharp tool with the blade at a right angle to the handle, used to shape pieces of wood'

name: to skin
description: 'strip or pull off the skin or hide of'

name: to stretch
description: 'make [something elastic] bigger or looser by pulling it'

name: to pull
description: 'use one's hand to make something move towards one or in the direction that one is moving'

name: to sweep
description: 'clean the dust/dirt from the floor/ground using a broom'

name: the broom
description: 'a large brush with a long handle, used for sweeping floors'

name: the tool
description: 'an artifact (such as a hammer, a saw or a screwdriver) held in one's hand to help one in performing a particular job'

name: the carpenter
description: 'someone whose job is making and repairing wooden objects'

name: to bore
description: 'make a deep round hole in a hard surface'

name: to hollow out
description: 'make a hole or empty space by removing the inside part of something'

name: the nail
description: 'a thin pointed piece of metal which one forces into a piece of wood with a hammer to fasten the wood to something else'

name: the glue
description: 'a sticky substance used for joining things together'

name: to forge
description: 'make something from a piece of metal by heating the metal and shaping it'

name: the anvil
description: 'a heavy iron block on which pieces of metal are shaped using a hammer'

name: to cast
description: 'form metal objects by pouring the molten metal into molds'

name: to mould/mold
description: 'form articles from clay or other plastic material by molding with the hands'

name: the mat
description: 'a small piece of thick rough material which covers part of the floor'

name: the rug
description: 'a piece of thick cloth or wool that is smaller than a carpet and is put on the floor as decoration'

name: the netbag
description: 'bag made of net used in Papua to carry things’

name: to carve
description: 'cut shapes out of wood or stone'

name: the chisel
description: 'a metal tool with a sharp edge, used to cut wood or stone'

name: the paint
description: 'a liquid that one puts on a surface to make it a particular colour'

name: to crouch
description: ‘lower one’s body close to the ground by bending one’s knees completely’

name: to have
description: 'have temporarily (including things that one does not strictly speaking possess)'

name: to take
description: 'seize a concrete object in the hand and hold it'

name: to grasp
description: 'take and hold something firmly with one's hands'

name: to hold
description: 'to have something in one's hand or arms'

name: to get
description: 'come into possession of something' (neutral between ‘obtain’ and ‘receive’)

name: to give
description: 'physical transfer of an object with one's hands that passes into possession of the recipient'

name: to give back
description: 'give something that was earlier in the recipient's possession'

name: to preserve
description: ‘save something/someone from being harmed or destroyed’

name: to rescue
description: 'make someone safe from danger or harm'

name: to destroy
description: 'damage something so badly that it cannot be repaired or so that it no longer exists'

name: the bill
description: ‘written list showing how much a customer has to pay’

name: the wages
description: 'the money a worker receives for the work done'

name: the merchant
description: 'someone who buys and sells goods in large quantities'

name: to share
description: 'let someone have part of something that belongs to oneself'

name: the fathom
description: ‘a unit of length (originally outstretched arms), equal to about 1.8 metres’

name: thick
description: (in dimension; as opposed to thick in density, e.g. thick soup, hair)

name: thin
description: (in dimension; as opposed to thin in density, e.g. thin soup, hair)

name: to count
description: 'count objects in a set in order to determine the total'

name: all
description: 'the complete set of' (applied to a conceptually countable and nonsingular noun)

name: many
description: 'a large number of' (applied to a conceptually countable and nonsingular noun)

name: some
description: 'a certain number of' (applied to a conceptually countable and nonsingular noun)

name: the crowd
description: 'a large number of people in one place'

name: the half
description: 'either of the two equal parts into which something is divided'

name: the pair
description: 'two things of the same kind that are used together'

name: to sniff
description: 'to inhale through one's nose in order to smell something'

name: brackish
description: brackish water: 'water that is not pure but is slightly salty'

name: to listen
description: 'pay attention to a sound that one can hear'

name: to touch
description: 'put one's hand on something/someone so that one can feel them'

name: to pinch
description: 'press a part of someone's flesh very tightly between one's finger and thumb (so that it hurts)'

name: to feel
description: 'touch something to get a tactile perception of it'

name: hard
description: 'difficult to press down, break or cut'

name: smooth
description: 'completely even/flat, so that the hand moves easiy over it'

name: dry
description: 'without water or liquid inside or on the surface'

name: the mind
description: 'the seat of intelligence (as opposed to 'heart’ or 'soul’ as the seat of emotions)'

name: to believe
description: 'be sure that someone is telling the truth'

name: the manner
description: ‘the way in which something is done or happens’

name: to mumble
description: ‘to say something too quietly and not clearly enough, so that it is difficult or impossible to hear’

name: to shriek
description: ‘to make a very high, loud sound’

name: to howl
description: ‘(dog/wolf/other mammal:) to make a long, loud sound’

name: the rattle
description: ‘a wooden instrument that makes a loud knocking noise [used by people watching football games]’

name: the people
description: 'the populace, the inhabitants of a country (as opposed to the ruling class)'

name: to command or order
description: 'tell someone to do something, using one's authority or power'

name: the sword
description: 'metal weapon with a handle, blade , and sheath'

name: the armour
description: ‘metal or leather clothing worn by soldiers in former times to protect their body’

name: the law
description: 'a rule that people in a particular country (or administrative area) must obey'

name: the court
description: '(the judge and/or the jury in a) place where all the information concerning a crime is given so that it can be judged'

name: to adjudicate
description: 'decide whether someone is guilty of a crime in court'

name: the judgment
description: 'official decision given by a judge or a court of law'

name: to swear
description: 'make a public official promise, especially in a court of law'

name: to condemn
description: to find guilty or to sentence

name: the arson
description: ‘deliberately setting fire to something to cause damage’

name: the altar
description: ‘a raised place on which religious rites are performed’

name: to worship
description: ‘to perform a rite in honor of a deity’

name: the tin/can
description: ‘hermetically sealed metal container for preserved food’

name: the bottle
description: ‘glass container for liquids with narrow neck’

name: the vagina
description: ‘the passage from a woman’s outer sexual organs to her womb’

name: the larch
description: a tree (Larix) of the pine family

name: to tan
description: ‘to make animal skin into leather by by treating it with tannin (=a kind of acid)’

name: the cone
description: ‘fruit of a pine or fir tree’

name: the vulva
description: ‘the outer part of a woman’s sexual organs’

name: the tumpline
description: 'a strap slung over the forehead or chest used (especially by native Americans) for carrying packs or loads'

name: the savanna
description: 'a large open grassland in tropical and subtropical regions'

name: the paddy
description: 'wet land in which rice is grown'

name: the loam
description: a rich soil consisting of a mixture of sand and clay and decaying organic materials

name: the agouti
description: A burrowing rodent of the genus Dasyprocta, native to tropical America and usually having brown fur streaked with gray

name: the Andean guinea pig
description: It is raised for food, medicine and ritual in the Andes

name: the capibara
description: A large semiaquatic rodent (Hydrochoerus hydrochaeris) of tropical South America

name: the hocco
description: the crested curassow, also called royal pheasant

name: the paca
description: A large nocturnal burrowing rodent of the genus Cuniculus, found in South and Central America

name: the ayahuasca
description: a psychoactive infusion prepared from the Banisteriopsis spp

name: the amomum
description: a genus of plants in the ginger family

name: the anatto
description: a derivative of the achiote trees of tropical regions of the Americas, used to produce a red food coloring

name: the Chinese rice flower
description: (Aglaia odorata), a shrub or small tree in the mahogany family, from south China and Indo-China, grown ornamentally for the handsome leaves and fragrant flowers, which are tiny, round, and yellow; clusters of them are used for leis

name: the creeper
description: specifically, an odorant plant that gorws in the bleak plateaus. sp. Micromeria nubigena.

name: the mortiño
description: Vaccinium mortinia, a dark red berry

name: the jowar
description: Sorghum is a genus of numerous species of grasses, some of which are raised for grain and many of which are used as fodder plants

name: the lupin
description: any plant of the genus Lupin; bearing erect spikes of usually purplish-blue flowers

name: the vetch
description: Any of various herbs of the genus Vicia, having pinnately compound leaves that terminate in tendrils and small, variously colored flowers.

name: the woody shrub
description: Plant whose wood is used for building huts

name: the yerba mate
description: k.o. leaves that are dried and made into an infusion like tea

name: to raise
description: to breed and care for to maturity (transitive)

name: the centigram
description: A metric unit of mass equal to one hundredth (10) of a gram.

name: the time(2)
description: the recurring occasion on which something happens

name: the state
description: the condition in which sth. or s.o. exists at a given time

name: the upper case or capital letter
Sir
description: epithet that precedes male given names

name: the certificate
description: a document issued by some authority and given to s.o. as a proof of sth.

name: the vote or ballot or pole
the license
description: the permission issued by some authority to legalize a certain state or recurring action

name: (interrogative)
description: The word is used in the interrogation and indicates doubt

name: nor
description: second part of the complex coordinating conjunction ‘neither – nor’
